full_text: Screened by NARA, 7/5/2023 2 2t 16 UNITED STATES DISTRICT COURT CENTRAL DISTRICT OF CALIFORNIA 12- CITIZEN APPLICANT INFORMATION INSTRUCTIONS 1. PLEASE PRINT CLEARLY. 2. This form is to be completed by each applicant for citizenship on the day of the final examination and given to the INS examiner. 3. The INS examiner will check whether the applicant is a Grant or a Denial then date and sign the form. 4. The INS examiner will send the original of this form to the U.S. District Court, retain one copy for INS records and give the second copy to the applicant. 5. IF YOU ARE INDICATING A NAME CHANGE ON THIS FORM, YOU MUST RETAIN YOUR APPLCIANT'S COPY OF THIS FORM WITH THE CERTIFICATE YOU WILL RECEIVE UPON THE TAKING OF THE OATH OF ALLEGIANCE. DO NOT LOSE IT.
